UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393284900412
AB  - The multi-product nature of the banking firm is examined utilizing the translog cost function. This analysis indicates that, contrary to conventional wisdom, natural monopoly, scale economies and product-specific decreasing costs are not robust characterizations of the banking industry. There is, however, evidence that the cost function is characterized by economies of scope. The implications of these results are discussed and extensions of this approach suggested.
