AB  - Interest rate models provide slightly better monthly forecasts and substantially better eight- and fourteen-month forecasts of inflation than a univariate time series model. The Livingston surveys underestimate eight- and fourteen-month inflation rates, especially during the high inflation period of 1978–81. In contrast, eight- and fourteen-month inflation forecasts extrapolated from one-month interest rates show little bias and track ex post eight- and fourteen-month inflation rates better than the survey forecasts.
