DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(84)90037-0
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393284900370
AB  - Fixed exchange rates can be maintained by different types of stabilization schemes. This paper takes a look at some alternative institutional settings and shows that there is an inherent redistribution mechanism in some of them that will influence the world allocation of consumption. An examination of the global adjustment to monetary disturbances illustrates some interesting implications of the institutional differences between alternative systems. The results suggest that the description of the international adjustment mechanism under fixed exchange rates given by the monetary approach to the balance-of-payments is valid only under quite restrictive assumptions.
ER  - 
